messages.message: I tested this on a couple of bank statements (my project (https://aihub-sandbox.internal.instabase.com/hub/apps/converse/944d2585-5b02-42f8-90a9-44c5c8f80be6)) and on one (`William Jones.pdf`), it extracts all the tables, but doesn't stitch together a multi-page table (is that expected?). On another (`William Lara.pdf`, it misses the second page of deposits.
Also this was pretty easy to try out - the settings panel makes it super easy! :smile:

Pls share the docs, I can look at why it didn't stitch the tables. In general FR detects tables on a page-by-page basis, with no previous context, so sometimes it gets the columns incorrectly, which hinders table stitching.
Yes Lydia - unable to open your project, if you can share the doc, we can try this out.
